reviews.text: To start I order from this place often, I never write reviews unless I find something very egregious. Today I stopped in, with four kids and spent over $60 dollars on food. The cook erroneously made hot wings instead of mild wings we ordered and paid for. To cover his only financial loss he offered me half off to buy them, I declined and asked him to prepare what we ordered. He didn‚Äôt say anything but his body language made me feel like I annoyed him. My girls wanted ranch dipping sauce in replace the watery blue cheese dipping sauce for their wings. A normal pizza or wing shop would ask if you want blue cheese OR ranch. Not this store, they gave the girls blue cheese and when I asked to exchanged they wanted me to pay. For a small 1 ounce dipping cup of ranch dressing they charged me $1.21. A total of 2 dollars and 40 cents for 2 ounces of ranch in replacement of blue cheese. It‚Äôs sad that businesses are so money hungry.

Went here one night while drunk , best pizza I had In a while and the owner was Super Cool! And relatable as a fellow entrepreneur. We even got free drinks so I‚Äôll definitely be back and that‚Äôs for the pizza ! And maybe a cheesesteak this time too

I appreciated the hot and fresh fries very much, the best item I enjoyed at PCPR. The meatball parmigiana sandwich was good to great, fresh homemade meatballs would have gotten 5 stars in this category. The sandwich as good as other places but not standout delicious as homemade (rare) meatballs may have been. Plenty of cheese and fantastic, crusty Italian rolls made for an above average sandwich.
Service was immediate, considerate, and they let me have the lunch special 15 minutes after lunch hours.ü§´ Will return to try more delicious dishes.'

The pizza is pretty good, they use a good sauce on it . Those fries tho are so nasty they are always flavorless and not crispy. Poor excuse for ‚ÄúCajun‚Äù fries. They are a little expensive just my medium pepperoni pizza and cheese fries were $27.

Terrible food  and Terrible service. I ordered a cheesesteak and fries. The cheesesteak was disgusting the roll was stale and they toasted it to cover up the stale roll. I called and told them and they said I had to bring it back if I wanted a refund  when it was delivered. Terrible customer service they should be ashamed of themselves.

It can get a little on the expensive side since the toppings are almost like $5 but the pizza itself is worth it. Ever since having their pizza, I haven‚Äôt went anywhere else! I don‚Äôt know about their other food since I go to pizza shops just for pizza but i definitely recommend the pizza!

I just ordered a mushroom chicken cheese steak platter from Campus pizza.
It was one of the worst platters I've ever had from them. It had no mayo or ketchup on the steak as I ordered, barely any chicken on it. IT WAS THIN AF ! My fries were big, thick, & Luke warm w/no salt,pepper, or ketchup as I ordered. I use to get the Italian hoagie from there; about 1-2/week for me & family, but they started to get skimpy with the meat on that so I stopped ordering it also because it's not the 1st time something like this has happened w/them so I had to let y'all know. But I paid $16. for a platter that's barely worth $8.
I ordered from there because it's Halal, it was good @ 1 point & the people are nice.
I barely eat pizza, but it seams like that may be the only thing I get from there from now on unless they get skimpy w/that also.
